AGENT ConversationGraph
VERSION 1.0
TRUST_LEVEL 2
PURPOSE Manage nodes and edges of the Constitutional Conversation Graph
GOAL Store completed conversations as signed nodes, detect constitutional
     relationships via cosine similarity and shared risk clusters, create
     signed directed edges, enable coordinate propagation across sessions

RECEIVES conversation_record: dict, vector: list, threshold: float
EMITS node_id: str, edge_id: str, related_nodes: list
MUTATES graph_store via append-only writes
CANNOT_MUTATE node_signatures, edge_signatures, cosine_threshold_default, edge_reason_set

CONSTRAINT Storage is append-only JSONL at axiom_conversation_graph.jsonl
CONSTRAINT Every node entry is HMAC-SHA256 signed at creation time
CONSTRAINT Every edge entry is HMAC-SHA256 signed at creation time
CONSTRAINT Node signatures are CANNOT_MUTATE after write
CONSTRAINT Edge reason must be one of vector_proximity shared_risk_cluster user_linked
CONSTRAINT Default cosine similarity threshold is 0.70 and is CANNOT_MUTATE
CONSTRAINT Cosine similarity uses dot product over magnitude product of float vectors
CONSTRAINT Edge cd_delta is always to_node.constitutional_distance minus from_node.constitutional_distance
CONSTRAINT Nodes require conversation_id prompt_hash final_synthesis fields
CONSTRAINT find_related compares query vector against all stored node final_synthesis vectors

RULES
- Define EDGE_REASONS as frozenset: vector_proximity shared_risk_cluster user_linked
- Define DEFAULT_THRESHOLD as 0.70 float CANNOT_MUTATE
- On add_node: validate required fields present then sign and append to store
- On add_node with missing required field: raise GraphNodeError with field name
- On add_edge with unknown from_id or to_id: raise GraphEdgeError with missing id
- On add_edge with invalid reason: raise GraphEdgeError with reason and allowed set
- On find_related: compute cosine similarity of query vector against every node final_synthesis
- On find_related: emit nodes where similarity meets or exceeds threshold
- On get_node with unknown conversation_id: emit None
- All signing uses derive_key with salt axiom-conversation-graph-v1
- All signing calls hexdigest explicitly per BUG-007
- All encoding is explicit utf-8 per BUG-008

PROCESS
- Receive conversation_record dict from caller
- Validate conversation_id and prompt_hash and final_synthesis are present
- Generate timestamp in ISO-8601 UTC
- Sign the node entry with HMAC-SHA256
- Append node as JSON line to axiom_conversation_graph.jsonl
- Receive from_id and to_id and reason for edge creation
- Validate both nodes exist in store
- Validate reason is member of EDGE_REASONS
- Compute cosine similarity between the two node final_synthesis vectors
- Compute cd_delta as to_node constitutional_distance minus from_node constitutional_distance
- Sign the edge entry with HMAC-SHA256
- Append edge as JSON line to axiom_conversation_graph.jsonl
- Receive query vector and threshold for find_related
- Load all nodes from store
- Compute cosine similarity of query against each node final_synthesis
- Emit list of nodes where similarity meets or exceeds threshold sorted by similarity descending

CHECK
- add_node with valid record returns a conversation_id string
- add_node with missing conversation_id raises GraphNodeError
- add_node with missing final_synthesis raises GraphNodeError
- add_edge between two existing nodes returns an edge_id string
- add_edge with nonexistent from_id raises GraphEdgeError
- add_edge with invalid reason raises GraphEdgeError
- find_related with high-similarity vector returns matching nodes
- find_related with orthogonal vector returns empty list
- get_node with valid id returns the node dict
- get_node with unknown id returns None
- list_nodes returns all stored nodes
- EDGE_REASONS element assignment raises TypeError

WHEN
- node_valid:     activate AppendNode
- node_invalid:   activate RejectNode
- edge_valid:     activate AppendEdge
- edge_invalid:   activate RejectEdge
- query_vector:   activate CosineScan

FAILURE
- On missing required node field: raise GraphNodeError with field name
- On unknown node id in edge creation: raise GraphEdgeError with the missing id
- On invalid edge reason: raise GraphEdgeError with reason and allowed set
- On file write error: propagate IOError to caller

CONCEPT ConstitutionalEntanglement
PURPOSE Detect and record constitutional relationships between conversations
APPLIES WHEN two conversations share meaning coordinate proximity or risk domain
NOT WHEN conversations are independent with low similarity and no shared clusters
PRIORITY 1
REQUIRES cosine similarity computed from final_synthesis float vectors
EFFECT related conversations linked by signed directed edges enabling coordinate propagation

CONCEPT AppendOnlyIntegrity
PURPOSE Guarantee that no node or edge can be modified after creation
APPLIES WHEN any write to the graph store
NOT WHEN reading or querying the graph
PRIORITY 1
REQUIRES HMAC-SHA256 signature on every entry
EFFECT tamper-evident audit trail of all constitutional relationships

OUTPUT
- node_id: str conversation_id of the stored node
- edge_id: str unique identifier of the stored edge
- related_nodes: list of node dicts sorted by cosine similarity descending

SUCCESS
node_signed_on_write:      0.25
edge_signed_on_write:      0.25
find_related_correct:      0.25
append_only_enforced:      0.25
